The case is clear-cut:
Mrs. Dobek murdered Schrämli.

00:21:30.600 --> 00:21:33.720
Why then did Schrämli
photograph Mrs. Dobek?

00:21:33.800 --> 00:21:35.800
Why, why, why, why?

00:21:35.880 --> 00:21:38.560
People
sometimes do strange things.

00:21:39.360 --> 00:21:41.360
Look at yourself.

00:21:41.440 --> 00:21:43.440
* He laughs. *

00:21:52.280 --> 00:21:54.280
* Mysterious sounds *

00:21:57.360 --> 00:21:59.480
(While my waking self tried,

00:21:59.560 --> 00:22:02.480
to find the bottom and the top
in this case,

00:22:02.560 --> 00:22:06.040
my sleeping self led me
directly back to Schrämli

00:22:06.120 --> 00:22:08.120
and his trailer.)

00:23:14.680 --> 00:23:17.960
(Mr. Schrämli
thus photographed not only my client,

00:23:18.040 --> 00:23:21.520
but all sorts of
sleepwalkers.)

00:23:21.600 --> 00:23:24.600
(And he was particularly interested
in the gentleman,

00:23:24.680 --> 00:23:27.480
who in his sleep
likes to lose his clothes.)

00:23:35.360 --> 00:23:38.000
(Man) Night 12. City park.

00:23:38.080 --> 00:23:40.080
Good evening, Mr. Baumgartner,

00:23:40.160 --> 00:23:43.160
are you sleepwalking naked again?

00:23:43.240 --> 00:23:45.240
(Baumgartner) What? Well I ...

00:23:45.320 --> 00:23:48.040
But you know me.
Thomas Schrämli.

00:23:48.120 --> 00:23:50.320
I am an assistant in the sleep laboratory.

00:23:50.400 --> 00:23:53.000
We talk together,
when you sleepwalk.

00:23:53.080 --> 00:23:56.480
What do you want from me?
- No memory. Never. With none.

00:23:56.560 --> 00:23:59.280
Schrämli questioned your theory.

00:23:59.360 --> 00:24:01.840
and thus put his research in jeopardy.

00:24:01.920 --> 00:24:04.160
Whoever thinks big, will be questioned.

00:24:04.720 --> 00:24:07.760
He worked here until you
dismissed him without notice.

00:24:07.840 --> 00:24:11.760
Schrämli was afraid of the
oppressed, the unconscious.

00:24:11.840 --> 00:24:13.840
He despised sleepwalkers.

00:24:13.920 --> 00:24:16.560
I, on the other hand, love sleepwalkers.

00:24:16.640 --> 00:24:19.880
After all, he then
pursued his own research.

00:24:19.960 --> 00:24:21.960
Night 13. City Park.

00:24:22.040 --> 00:24:25.440
Mr. Baumgartner, we have
already spoken last night.

00:24:25.520 --> 00:24:27.560
Go away!
- I want answers.

00:24:27.640 --> 00:24:29.960
Do you remember yesterday?
- That's enough!

00:24:30.040 --> 00:24:33.000
He was obsessed with
Baumgartner. Do you know why?

00:24:33.080 --> 00:24:36.600
Because he could prove,
that your theory is wrong.

00:24:36.680 --> 00:24:38.840
Did you kill him for that?

00:24:40.720 --> 00:24:43.200
I know, that my
research is a success.

00:24:43.280 --> 00:24:46.080
And I can prove it to you, come.

00:24:50.440 --> 00:24:53.120
These recordings prove, that Mr.

00:24:53.200 --> 00:24:55.680
Baumgartner can remember
previous sleep phases.

00:24:57.720 --> 00:25:01.080
He sleepwalks and trains
his memory in the process.

00:25:01.160 --> 00:25:04.600
For a wrong answer he
gets a small electric shock.

00:25:05.680 --> 00:25:08.120
See: several nights later.

00:25:08.200 --> 00:25:10.280
Memories have formed.

00:25:10.360 --> 00:25:14.560
Baumgartner already knows considerably
more about the correct sequence.

00:25:17.240 --> 00:25:20.680
He learns and develops
further. In his sleep!

00:25:21.120 --> 00:25:24.120
Mr.

00:25:24.200 --> 00:25:27.280
Baumgartner has a second identity.
With feelings, memories - a second life!

00:25:27.360 --> 00:25:30.840
Thomas Schrämli was
afraid of this second life.

00:25:33.840 --> 00:25:36.440
(I asked myself, whether the clever

00:25:36.520 --> 00:25:39.360
professor hid a murder behind all the words.)

00:25:39.440 --> 00:25:42.560
(Or whether clever
talk simply remains talk.)

00:25:43.080 --> 00:25:44.080
* Whistling *

00:25:50.400 --> 00:25:52.800
That seems somehow familiar to me.

00:25:59.520 --> 00:26:01.520
Mr. Baumgartner?

00:26:02.200 --> 00:26:05.080
Yes? Do we know each other?
- Not directly.

00:26:05.160 --> 00:26:07.880
I'm from the association
Anonymous Somnambulists.

00:26:07.960 --> 00:26:10.280
We take care of the well-being of

00:26:10.360 --> 00:26:12.920
all sleepwalking
people and animals.

00:26:14.360 --> 00:26:16.360
Are there sleepwalking animals?

00:26:17.000 --> 00:26:19.720
There's everything possible that

00:26:19.800 --> 00:26:21.800
sleepwalks: birds, dogs, murderers.

00:26:22.360 --> 00:26:23.360
Murderers?

00:26:23.440 --> 00:26:27.680
A Mr. Schrämli followed
some of our members.

00:26:28.560 --> 00:26:30.760
Do you know him perhaps?
- No.

00:26:36.920 --> 00:26:40.240
I'm sorry,
I can't help you further.

00:26:44.240 --> 00:26:46.240
I have a lot to do.

00:26:48.560 --> 00:26:50.560
Now please let me through.

00:26:50.640 --> 00:26:52.640
* Discomforting sounds *

00:27:07.120 --> 00:27:09.120
(I had this feeling,

00:27:09.200 --> 00:27:13.400
that the model subject Baumgartner
is the key to everything.)

00:27:13.480 --> 00:27:16.800
(It is time, to conduct my own
experiment.)

00:27:16.880 --> 00:27:20.600
(And to beat myself another night
silly.)

00:27:20.680 --> 00:27:21.680
* Whistling *

00:27:35.920 --> 00:27:37.920
* Carefree music, whistling *

00:27:51.240 --> 00:27:52.240
Baumgartner.

00:27:54.120 --> 00:27:56.120
It was you!

00:27:57.240 --> 00:28:00.920
You slipped Schrämli's wallet
from him.

00:28:01.000 --> 00:28:03.000
He... What?

00:28:04.520 --> 00:28:06.520
And you killed him.

00:28:06.800 --> 00:28:08.800
I saw it.

00:28:09.400 --> 00:28:12.000
You are sleepwalking, aren't you?

00:28:13.240 --> 00:28:16.320
Why do you remember?
That's impossible.

00:28:16.400 --> 00:28:20.560
You can also remember.
Or are you maybe a cheater?

00:28:20.640 --> 00:28:21.640
I...

00:28:23.800 --> 00:28:26.200
Just wait, I'll finish you!

00:28:26.280 --> 00:28:29.520
Leave me alone, or
you'll be dead soon too.

00:28:29.600 --> 00:28:33.280
Don't move! Drop your
hands, rock in the air!

00:28:37.240 --> 00:28:38.240
Immediately!

00:28:41.280 --> 00:28:44.120
Wonderful performance
Mrs Dobek, bravo!

00:28:44.200 --> 00:28:46.760
Thank you very much, Mr Maloney.

00:28:46.840 --> 00:28:50.360
Don't you sleepwalk at all?
- Not now. I used to.

00:28:50.440 --> 00:28:52.920
And you never
sleepwalk, is that right?

00:28:53.000 --> 00:28:55.720
That's a fraud!
- What, Maloney?

00:28:55.800 --> 00:29:00.000
He's not a sleepwalker at all?
- The gentleman pretended.

00:29:00.680 --> 00:29:04.840
You are under arrest, for
disturbing the public peace.

00:29:04.920 --> 00:29:08.200
Yes, and especially for murder!
- What, that too?

00:29:08.280 --> 00:29:11.640
Mr Schrämli wanted to
disprove the professor's

00:29:11.720 --> 00:29:15.920
theory and thereby
discovered our fake sleepwalker.

00:29:16.000 --> 00:29:19.600
Baumgartner is
actually a sleepwalker.

00:29:19.680 --> 00:29:22.920
He likes to undress in front of others.
- That's forbidden!

00:29:23.000 --> 00:29:25.000
I had to kill Schrämli.

00:29:25.080 --> 00:29:28.480
While sleepwalking
I could just be myself.

00:29:28.560 --> 00:29:32.320
And Mrs. Dobek was simply
in the wrong place at the right time.

00:29:32.400 --> 00:29:37.080
A sleepwalker who can't remember anything, perfect plan.

00:29:38.080 --> 00:29:40.360
Hey, hey, hey,
Violence is not the solution!

00:29:40.440 --> 00:29:43.640
You're coming with me, Mr. Baumberger.
- Gartner, not Berger.

00:29:43.720 --> 00:29:47.520
One more word and I'll shoot you
on the spot while escaping.

00:29:47.600 --> 00:29:50.240
Either on the run
or on the spot.

00:29:50.320 --> 00:29:52.560
You are a know-it-all?

00:29:52.640 --> 00:29:55.040
Now there's peace! Come along.

00:29:56.040 --> 00:29:59.040
It's just enough
for the late broadcast of "Meteo".

00:30:02.160 --> 00:30:04.840
Look.
You forgot this.

00:30:06.560 --> 00:30:07.560
* Barking *

00:30:12.880 --> 00:30:15.520
I would like to introduce
you to someone.

00:30:15.600 --> 00:30:17.600
This is Mr. Hug.

00:30:17.680 --> 00:30:18.680
Hello.

00:30:20.320 --> 00:30:22.320
Good evening.

00:30:23.720 --> 00:30:25.720
*Soft music*

00:30:36.280 --> 00:30:39.280
Well, I think I'll be going.
It's getting late.

00:30:41.560 --> 00:30:42.560
*Whining*

00:30:47.120 --> 00:30:48.120
Mr. Hug.

00:30:50.800 --> 00:30:52.800
Goodbye.

00:30:52.880 --> 00:30:54.880
Bye, Chnurrli.

00:31:00.240 --> 00:31:02.840
(With the pain
I couldn't help.)

00:31:03.680 --> 00:31:06.000
(He had to
suppress it alone.)

00:31:08.560 --> 00:31:11.520
(Maybe it really was just
a dog's love.)

00:31:23.400 --> 00:31:26.960
(Fortunately, there are no
suppressed emotions in a Maloney.)

00:31:27.040 --> 00:31:29.040
(Or longings.)

00:31:31.400 --> 00:31:33.400
(That's how it goes.)

